        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="Kali149-kilavi">itu varaivu nīṭṭittuḻit talaiviyatu āṟṟāmai kūṟit talaivaṉai varaivu kaṭāyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en"></p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="Kali149">
              <l>niraitimil kaḷiṟākat tiraiyoli paṟaiyākak</l>
              <l>karaicēr puḷḷiṉat tañciṟai paṭaiyāka</l>
              <l>varaicukāl kiḷarntaṉṉa vuravunīrc cērppakēḷ;</l>
              <l rend="space">kaṟpittā ṉeñcaḻuṅkap pakarntuṇṇāṉ viccaikkaṭ</l>
              <l>ṭappittāṉ poruḷēpōṟ ṟamiyavē tēyumā</l>
              <l>loṟkattu ḷutaviyārk kutavātāṉ maṟṟava</l>
              <l>ṉeccattu ḷāyiṉumaḵ teṟiyātu viṭātēkāṇ;</l>
              <l rend="space">kēḷirka ṇeñcaḻuṅkak keḻuvuṟṟa celvaṅka</l>
              <l>ḷāḷilāṉ kuṭiyēpōṟ ṟamiyavē tēyumāl</l>
              <l>cūḷpoytta maṉattavaṉ viṉaivāyppiṉ maṟṟavaṉ</l>
              <l>vāḷvāynaṉ ṟāyiṉumaḵ teṟiyātu viṭātēkāṇ;</l>
              <l rend="space">āṅku,</l>
              <l>aṉaittiṉip peruma vataṉilai niṉaittukkāṇ</l>
              <l>ciṉaiiya vēnta ṉeyiṟpuṟat tiṟutta</l>
              <l>viṉaivaru paruvaral pōlat</l>
              <l>tuṉaivaru neñcamoṭu varuntiṉaḷ peritē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
              <l>O man from the coast of strong waters that seem to express the time of the king(?),</l>
              <l>with boats in rows as male elephants, with the sound of the waves as drums,</l>
              <l corresp="1-3">and with the pretty wings of the flocks of birds that join the shore, listen:</l>
              <l></l>
              <l>Like the wealth of him who failed in knowledge, not absorbing when announced that the heart</l>
              <l>of the one who taught [him] suffers will dwindle all alone,</l>
              <l>He who does not help those who helped [him] in weakness, even though in his</l>
              <l corresp="4-7">remainder it is, that won’t attack [and] won’t let go, see.</l>
              <l></l>
              <l>Like the family of one without effort for riches who felt friendship </l>
              <l>when the hearts of [his] kinfolk suffers will dwindle all alone,</l>
              <l>if the work of a king who lied in [his] vows succeeds, even though his</l>
              <l corresp="8-11">sword’s edge may be good, that won’t cut [and] won’t let go, see.</l>
              <l></l>
              <l corresp="12">Thus,</l>
              <l>that much now, great man, think of its state [and] see:</l>
              <l>like the affliction that comes to the works</l>
              <l>when outside the fortress an angry king camps,</l>
              <l corresp="13-16">she suffered greatly with a heart that comes for [its] mate.</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
